          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\colon  X_\bullet \to  S]]></fr:tex> be an augmented simplicial topological space.
    For every sheaf <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>, we have a morphism
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[       \varphi \colon  F       \to  a_*a^*F     ]]></fr:tex>
    from the adjunction <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a^*\dashv  a_*]]></fr:tex>.
    This morphism derives to a morphism of functors from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {D}^+(S)]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {D}^+(S)]]></fr:tex>, namely

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2366</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-5.3.1.1</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-5.3.1.1.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>5.3.1.1</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-iii-5.3.1</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         \varphi \colon \mathrm {Id}         \to  \mathrm {R} a_*a^*.       \tag{5.3.1.1}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
